content:
I understand the instruction. I need to form an equilateral triangle with two other robots. The center of the triangle should be at (150, 100), and the side length should be 100. One of us must be on the edge but not the vertex. First, I need to find my current position and orientation. Then, I need to calculate the positions of the three vertices of the triangle. Finally, I will decide which vertex I should occupy.

```
[
  { "cmd": "sense" }
]
```

I see that trial2_robot1 is also trying to form the triangle. I should collaborate with it. I will broadcast my position and orientation to trial2_robot1.

```
[
  { "cmd": "broadcast", "data": "This is trial2_robot3: My position is (155, 14) and my orientation is 255. I am ready to collaborate." }
]
```

I see that trial2_robot4 is going to Vertex 3 (63.4, 50). I need to consider this when making a plan with trial2_robot1 and trial2_robot2. I will wait for trial2_robot1 to make a plan first.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 10000 }
]
```

Okay, trial2_robot4 has moved to a position on the edge between Vertex 3 and Vertex 1. I am still waiting for trial2_robot1 to come up with a plan. I will continue to wait.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 10000 }
]
```

My current position is (78.9, 50.0), and my target position was (78.87, 50). I am close enough to my target. trial2_robot2 confirmed that it is at its target. trial2_robot4 thinks that we have successfully formed an equilateral triangle. I confirm that I am at my target.

```
[
  { "cmd": "broadcast", "data": "This is trial2_robot3: I am at my target. I confirm that we have formed an equilateral triangle." }
]
```
